class 
Kubectl is used to manage the setup while Kubeadm is user to create the whole setup/cluster ----- Interview question can kubectl be used to bootstrap and create a cluster --- 
kubeadm is k8 administation 

Kubectl full form --- K8s control 
same question can be asked as what is K8 -- command line tool used to interact and manage the show 


COmmands ----- 
kubectl run pod-name --image=imagename ------------------------------ to "run" the pod 
ex - kubetcl run ngnix-demo

Kubectl get pods or kubectl get pods -o ---------------------------- to "get" the details of any pods

kubectl describe pods nhinx-demo ----------------------------------- will give the detailed information "describe" the item

kubectl delete pod pod-name ----------------------------------------will delete the details 
ex -  kubectl delete pod nginx-demo 

kubectl create deployment deplouname --image=imagename ------------will crearte the deployment 
ex ---kubectl create deployment depl-demo --image=nginx

kubeclt expose deloyment deplyment_name --port:80 --target-port=80 --------------expose command 
ex -kubeclt expose deloyment depl-demo --port:80 --target-port=80

kubectl edit -f [filename]/[resounrce]   ----------------------------------to edit 
ex- kubectl edit -f deployment deplo-demo   

kubectl apply -f filename ----------------------------------------------to apply 


